text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia schinoides is a shrub or tree indigenous to Australia. It has also been introduced into Kenya and Zimbabwe and it is cultivated there. A common name for the plant in Australia is green cedar wattle.
text.Description: Acacia schinoides grows to a height of 2 to 10 metres (7 to 33 ft)  In summer it bears cream-colored, ball-shaped flowers. It is a, "Fast-growing tree in well-composted soil."
text.Uses: The shrub makes a good garden hedge.
text.Natural growing conditions:
Acacia schinoides can withstand frosts as low as −7 °C.  It does well in both shade and sun.
